{ 4...c5  makes little sense as we can simply push ahead with  5.d5  d6  6.f4  Gaining even more space.  6...g6  7.Nf3  Bg7  8.c4  Nbd7  9.O-O  O-O  10.e5  ±  Is a Benoni horribly gone wrong for Black. White has achieved the e5 break and Black hasn't managed to create any counterplay on the queenside. }
